I never said they'd make people happy, just that Euro/Asian guilds will always have a significant advantage over US guilds as long as they can share servers.  <br>
And I really hope you aren't trying to say that the random spawns fixed a damn thing, laf.  Most mobs still spawn before US guilds can get online on patch day.  And even if they don't, US guilds have about a 5-6 hour window where a mob can spawn and they can get to it.  If it spawns before that window, it's dead to Asian/Euro guild.  If it spawns after that window, it waits for a couple hours til a Asain guild gets it.  Randomizing the spawns did exactly zilch to solve the problem.<br>
As far as you quitting if they force you to move, I can understand that.  I wouldn't want to move from a server where I log on, rub my hands together in anticipation, and freely choose from a list of currently spawned mobs while US guilds are still at work.  <br>
I'd be pissed if they made me leave too.  But as I said, I'd try to be sympathetic but I don't think I'd do too good a job.<br>
<br>
Btw, please don't take this as an anti-Euro/Asian rant.  It's not.  It's simply a statement of the way things are and why they will not change as things are done now.  I don't hold my lack of mobs to kill due to the Asian/Euro timezone advantage against those guilds, I place the blame squarely on Verant for not addressing this issue.  <br>
I'm happy that you all have stuff to kill, it sucks when you don't.  At the same time, though, don't expect me to feel sympathy if you are forced to play on even footing with other guilds on a server when US guilds currently don't even get that chance.<br>
