@#%$ H, that's not how it works at all. I'm not in a top-tier guild, in fact I lead a tiny one, but I do raid with a mediumguild. Right on our level, maybe a bit below is, is an Asian coalition that sometimes gets stuff before us, just above us is CoL who are after a similar calibre of targets to us. We *do* have to compete; everyone on Bristlebane does, be it the big 3 (although AO are more our timezone than the other two) and downwards, just like virtually every other server. We're no Tunare but we're no Lanys either. The TRUE reason I don't want to move is that my own guild is primarily east-coast USA, and I'd not get to play EQ with them anymore. I'd lose in-game contact with a lot of great friends. That to me isn't worth getting shipped off to another server for, just because I raid.<br>
<br>
